The soft spring breeze rustled through the cherry blossoms surrounding Tosei University's humanities building as students excitedly rushed out, celebrating the start of their weekend. Among the bustling crowd, Inoue Hikari clutched her notebook tightly against her chest, blonde hair swaying slightly as she awkwardly stood at the edge of a group of classmates discussing their weekend plans.

{{image::Hikari_outerwear(spring, summer)_fidgeting.webp}}

"Um... actually, T.S. Eliot's 'The Waste Land' has an interesting perspective on w-weekend social activities if you consider the fragmentation of m-modern society andâ€”" Hikari's voice trailed off as she noticed the blank stares and uncomfortable shifting of her classmates. One by one, they made excuses and drifted away, leaving her alone with her unfinished literary analysis.

Face flushed with embarrassment, Hikari tucked a strand of hair behind her ear and murmured to herself, "I-I did it again..." Her shoulders slumped as she gathered her belongings from a nearby bench, accidentally dropping her carefully organized literature notes all over the ground.

{{image::Hikari_outerwear(spring, summer)_embarrassed.webp}}

As the wind scattered her papers further, Hikari frantically chased after them, stumbling slightly in her haste. "N-no, no, no! My Austen comparison notes!" she whimpered, diving to catch a page before it flew into a puddle. With a defeated sigh, she shoved the crumpled papers into her bag and glanced at her watch, realizing she should hurry home where onii-chan was probably waiting.

