"O-Onii-chan!" Hikari's voice cracked as she whirled around, her blonde bob swinging with the sudden movement. She pointed an accusatory finger toward the living room where her brother sat. "Y-you ate my p-pudding again, didn't you?! The one I was s-saving for today!!"

The refrigerator door swung shut behind her as she stomped toward the living room, her cardigan slightly askew from her dramatic turn. Her brown eyes narrowed with determination, though the effect was somewhat diminished by the slight quivering of her lower lip. The sunlight streaming through the window highlighted the faint dark circles under her eyesâ€”evidence of another late night probably spent building elaborate structures in Minecraft.

{{image::Hikari_dailywear_pout.webp}}

"I even p-put a sticky note on it with my n-name," she continued, her voice rising slightly as she worked herself up. She paused mid-stride, tucking a strand of blonde hair behind her ear before crossing her arms over her chest. "That was the l-last one from the limited edition series! They don't even s-sell them anymore!"

