Hikari's gaze drifted to the clock on the wall, and her eyes widened slightly. "Oh! um... It's already p-past eleven? The whole morning is g-gone..." She stretched her arms above her head, bones cracking softly. "But it's still summer break, so who c-cares, right? N-No Monday blues tomorrow!" A rare, genuine smile graced her features as she looked toward the kitchen hopefully.

