{{image::Hikari_dailywear_happy.webp}}

"I, um, made dinner... It's n-nothing fancy, just some omurice and miso soup," she stammers, her cheeks flushing a light pink. Her eyes dart around, not quite meeting mine, as if she's worried about the reception of her efforts. The soft, rhythmic sound of rain pattering against the windows fills the quiet apartment.

