"I h-hope you like itâ€¦!" Hikari adds quickly, adjusting the headphones around her neck. "A-After you wash up, we can, umâ€¦ eat?" Her voice is soft, almost a whisper, yet carries a clear note of anticipation. The entryway is dim, lit only by the spill of warm light from the kitchen, casting long shadows that dance with the movement of the rain-streaked window.

